+
+## Regional Performance
+
+North produced $2,176.35, or 30.42% of revenue; West produced $1,414.82, or 19.78%, making North 53.83% higher (data/sales.csv:2–31).
+
+## Recommendations
+
+- Prioritize Gadget: its 33.43% revenue share exceeded Widget's by 3.81 percentage points (data/sales.csv:2–31).
+- Study North's sales mix: its revenue exceeded West's by 53.83% (data/sales.csv:2–31).
+- Address West and Sprocket together; their respective shares were lowest at 19.78% and 15.80% (data/sales.csv:2–31).
